snippet: Excitement over the interim agreement, which will ease some provisions of the American-led sanctions on Iran but essentially leave all of them in place, has not extended to American companies.
abstract: Critics of Iran in Congress and elsewhere have expressed dismay over the European trade missions that have taken place since an interim nuclear deal was agreed to in principle; excitement over the agreement, which will ease some provisions of the American-led sanctions on Iran, has not extended to American companies, which remain extremely wary.
lead_paragraph: Excitement over the interim agreement, which will ease some provisions of the American-led sanctions on Iran but essentially leave all of them in place, has not extended to American companies.

headline.main: Sanctions Eased, Iran Gets Feelers From Old Trading Partners
headline.print_headline: Deal Sets Off Many Feelers Toward Iran
